# 📦 SUMMARY  
# This URL opens Jenkins' **Configure Tools** page in the web UI, where you can set up tools like JDK, Git, Maven, or Docker for Jenkins jobs.  
# Language/Platform: Web URL (used in browser)  
# What you'll learn: Navigating Jenkins web interface, configuring global tool settings  
# Outcome: You’ll be able to define versions and paths for build tools Jenkins will use during job execution  
# Why this matters: Without proper tool configuration, Jenkins jobs that depend on them will fail (e.g., builds needing Maven or Git)  

# ------------------------------  
# 🧩 SECTION TITLE: Open Jenkins Configure Tools Page  
# ------------------------------  
http://<your-server-ip>:8080/manage/configureTools/  
# ✅ What it does: Directs your browser to Jenkins’ tool configuration page at your server’s IP on port 8080  
# 🧠 Why it matters: This page lets you define installation paths or automatic installers for tools needed by Jenkins pipelines  

# ------------------------------  
# ✅ NOTES / GOTCHAS / TIPS  
# ------------------------------  
# - Replace `<your-server-ip>` with the actual IP of your Jenkins host (e.g., `192.168.1.100`).  
# - You must be logged into Jenkins with admin privileges to access this page.  
# - Tools configured here become available globally to all jobs and pipelines.  
# - Common tools to configure:  
#   - **Git** for SCM checkout  
#   - **JDK** for Java-based builds  
#   - **Maven/Gradle** for Java project builds  
#   - **Docker** for containerized build environments  
# - For Jenkins running behind a firewall, ensure port 8080 is open.  
